            <scopecontent id="aspace_33b17be63f0834a283175bcfedbf5f7d">
               <head>Scope and Contents</head>
               <p>Series II consists of correspondence, financial records, invitations, and estate documents. Correspondence during Perkins's lifetime is fragmentary and relates chiefly to his social and political activity and to legal affairs, but does not comprehensively document his official duties as California legislator and governor. Correspondence and papers after 1923 relate chiefly to Perkins's estate. Financial records relate chiefly to the business of Goodall, Nelson &amp; Perkins (later Goodall, Perkins &amp; Co.).</p>
            </scopecontent>
